This paper is about object detection using deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks for this task, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes a new model for object detection, which involves designing the architecture of the neural network, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of saliency-inspired models, which is a topic that falls under neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed model on image recognition benchmarks, which is a topic that falls under multimedia (cs.MM).
